1. Otišli smo na *plažu* da se sunčamo. (We went to the *beach* to sunbathe.)
2. Nije bilo mnogo ljudi na *plaži* jer je bilo oblačno. (There weren't many people on the *beach* because it was cloudy.)
3. Pijesak na *plaži* bio je vrlo topao zbog sunca. (The sand on the *beach* was very warm because of the sun.)
4. Plivanje u *plažnom* moru je jedna od najpopularnijih aktivnosti na odmoru. (Swimming in the *beach* sea is one of the most popular activities on vacation.)
5. Uradili smo *plažni* piknik i jeli sendviče na obali. (We had a *beach* picnic and ate sandwiches on the shore.)
6. Zaštitio sam se od sunca kapom koju sam kupio na *plaži*. (I protected myself from the sun with a hat I bought at the *beach*.)
7. Ovo je najljepša *plaža* na cijelom ostrvu. (This is the most beautiful *beach* on the whole island.)
8. Na *plaži* smo se igrali odbojku s drugim ljudima. (We played volleyball with other people on the *beach*.)
9. Nismo mogli naći slobodnu *plažnu* stolicu pa smo sjeli na peškir. (We couldn't find a free *beach* chair, so we sat on a towel.)
10. Na *plaži* je bilo puno djeci koja su se igrala u vodi. (There were many children playing in the water on the *beach*.)

Note: The word "plažu" is in its basic form (nominative singular) in sentence 1, and in other forms in the remaining sentences, depending on their grammatical function within the sentence.